{
  "final_answer": "## AI Segment's Contribution to the Consolidated GAAP-to-Adjusted-EBITDA Bridge (FY2025)\n\n### Consolidated Bridge (Net Income → Adjusted EBITDA)\n\n| Adjustment Line Item | Consolidated ($M) |\n|:---|---:|\n| Depreciation & amortization | 6,701 |\n| Share-based compensation | 1,947 |\n| Restructuring charges | 487 |\n| Impairments | 38 |\n| Interest expense | 1,945 |\n| Interest income | (492) |\n| Other (income) expense, net | 177 |\n| Provision for income taxes | 718 |\n| **Total Consolidated Adjustment** | **11,521** |\n\n*(Net income of $(4,937)M + $11,521M in adjustments = Adjusted EBITDA of $6,584M)*\n\n### AI Segment's Adjustments (Income from Operations → Segment Adjusted EBITDA)\n\n| Adjustment Line Item | AI Segment ($M) | % of Consolidated Line |\n|:---|---:|---:|\n| Depreciation & amortization | 3,568 | 53.25% |\n| Share-based compensation | 1,063 | 54.60% |\n| Restructuring charges | 487 | 100.00% |\n| Impairment | — | 0.00% |\n| **Total AI Segment Adjustment** | **5,118** | |\n\n### Result\n\n$$\\frac{\\text{AI Segment Adjustments}}{\\text{Total Consolidated Adjustments}} = \\frac{5{,}118}{11{,}521} = \\mathbf{44.42\\%}$$\n\n**The AI segment contributed $5,118 million in adjustments, representing 44.42% of the total $11,521 million consolidated GAAP-to-Adjusted-EBITDA bridge for FY2025.**\n\nKey observations:\n- The AI segment accounts for **100% of all restructuring charges** ($487M) in the consolidated entity.\n- The AI segment represents over half of consolidated D&A (53.25%) and SBC (54.60%), reflecting the capital- and compensation-intensive nature of the xAI operations (retrospectively recast into all periods).\n- The remaining 55.58% of the consolidated bridge consists of adjustments from the Space and Connectivity segments ($4,055M in operating-level adjustments) plus corporate/unallocated items ($2,348M in interest, other income, and tax adjustments that are not allocated to segments).\n\n{\n  \"sources\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\",\n      \"name\": \"SpaceX S-1 Filing (Filed May 20, 2026)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
